cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the recognition of handwritten numerals using statistical discriminant functions and geometric features. The use of discriminant functions and geometric features suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of statistical methods for classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
